<dl id="n08126d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08126d">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08126d"> 126(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> daisy chains / berries, discs of bronze</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">To count <font color="green">[prayers]</font> accurately &hellip; already in the eleventh and twelfth centuries a practice had come in of using pebbles, berries, or discs of bone threaded on a string. <small> <a name="CECRA" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CECRA"><cite title="source">&ldquo;Coemgen&rdquo;, &ldquo;Rosary&rdquo; and &ldquo;Albigenses&rdquo;</cite></a> <cite a>Catholic Encyclopaedia</cite></a> (1911) XIII, &lsquo;Rosary&rsquo; 185b</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
